Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Once boiling, add @rigatoni pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

> Reserve 1 1/2 cups for 4 servings.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @shallot{1}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and grate @zucchini{1} on the largest holes of a #box grater{}.

Place zucchini in the center of a clean #kitchen towel{}. Gather into a tight bundle and squeeze over the sink to remove as much liquid as possible.

> Alternatively, place grated zucchini in a fine-mesh strainer and press down with a spatula.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, shallot, @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and mostly cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Add @tomato paste{1.5%ounce} to pan with beef. Cook, stirring, until tomato paste is well combined and beef is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in zucchini, garlic, and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until zucchini is tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}, @beef stock concentrate{1}, 1/2 cup reserved pasta cooking water (ladle straight from the pot if pasta isn't finished cooking yet), and @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}. Simmer until sauce has slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use 2/3 cup pasta cooking water and 1 tsp sugar. If you've got some on hand, add a pinch of chili flakes for a spicy kick.

Reduce heat to medium low. Stir drained rigatoni, half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, and @butter{1%tablespoon} into pan with sauce until combined.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP butter. If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between plates. Top with remaining Parmesan and serve.